public class PowerOfThree {
    public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        while (n % 3 == 0) {
            n /= 3;
        }

        return n == 1;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n = 27;
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(n)); // Output: true

        n = 0;
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(n)); // Output: false

        n = -1;
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(n)); // Output: false
    }
}
```

And here is a Java solution to the problem without using loops/recursion:

