public class PowerOfThree {
    public static boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        return n > 0 && Math.pow(3, (int)(Math.log10(n) / Math.log10(3))) == n;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int n = 27;
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(n)); // Output: true

        n = 0;
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(n)); // Output: false

        n = -1;
        System.out.println(isPowerOfThree(n)); // Output: false
    }
}
```

Both solutions have a time complexity of O(log(n)) and a space complexity of O(1).

